works.description: Recently, Luxury Beverage Company of the United Kingdom gave us the Isabella’s Islay, the world’s most expensive whisky at $6.2 million and now, we have the world’s most expensive liquor. Created in collaboration by Liverpool-based Stuart Hughes and Italian distillery Antica Distilleria Russo, the D’Amalfi Limoncello Supreme liquor costs a whopping £27 million (about $44 million).
